# Geist Design System (`@t2000/ui`)

`@t2000/ui` (`packages/ui`) is the **single source of truth** for the Geist Design System across the whole t2000 brand family — t2000 (`apps/web`, `apps/gateway`) and Audric (`audric/apps/web-v2`) all consume it. There is no second token system. Don't fork it, don't re-vendor Geist, don't hardcode hex.

## Two-layer model (the contract)

```
@t2000/ui  ──────────────▶  LAYER 1: primitives (shared, brand-neutral)
(packages/ui)               · raw Geist ramps + base tokens  → src/tokens/*.css
                            ·   --ds-* ramps, --fg, --bg, --bg-elevated, etc.
                            · shadcn/ui components             → src/primitives/*.tsx
                            · Tailwind v3 preset               → src/tailwind-preset.ts
                            · cn(), Sonner toaster
        │
        ▼
  each app's globals.css ─▶  LAYER 2: brand-semantic mapping (per-app)
                            · @import "@t2000/ui/tokens"
                            · map primitives → shadcn semantic tokens for THIS brand
                            ·   e.g. --background: var(--bg); --signal: var(--ds-teal-700)
```

**Layer 1 (`@t2000/ui`) is shared. Layer 2 (the semantic mapping) is per-brand and lives in the app.** A brand changes its look by re-mapping the shared primitives in its own `globals.css` — never by editing primitive values in `@t2000/ui` (that would move every brand at once).

## What `@t2000/ui` exports

| Export | What |
|---|---|
| `@t2000/ui` | `cn` + shadcn primitives: `Button`, `Card`, `Badge`, `Table`, `Separator`, `Dialog`, `Sheet`, `DropdownMenu`, `Accordion`, `Command`, `ScrollArea`, `Skeleton`, `Tabs`, `Tooltip` |
| `@t2000/ui/toaster` | Sonner toaster |
| `@t2000/ui/tokens` | Geist primitives (`--ds-*` ramps, `--fg`, `--bg`) — the base layer every app imports |
| `@t2000/ui/tokens/page` · `/responsive` · `/theme` | page-level vars, responsive scale, the Tailwind v4 `@theme` block |
| `@t2000/ui/tailwind-preset` | Tailwind v3 preset mapping `--ds-*` → `bg-background` / `text-foreground` / `bg-card` / `ring-ring` … |

## How apps wire it

**Tailwind v4 apps** (`apps/web`, `apps/gateway`) — import the token CSS in `globals.css`:

```css
@import "tailwindcss";
@import "@t2000/ui/tokens";
@import "@t2000/ui/tokens/page";
@import "@t2000/ui/tokens/responsive";
@import "@t2000/ui/tokens/theme";
```

**Tailwind v3 apps** — extend the preset instead:

```ts
import t2000UiPreset from '@t2000/ui/tailwind-preset';
export default { presets: [t2000UiPreset], content: [...] };
```

Then write shadcn-idiomatic classes (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `border-border`, `ring-ring`) — they resolve to Geist values automatically.

## Rules

1. **Never hardcode color.** No raw hex, no Tailwind default palette (`gray-500`, `bg-white`). Every value resolves through a Geist token.
2. **Never edit primitive values to restyle one brand.** Re-map in that app's `globals.css` (Layer 2). Editing `@t2000/ui` tokens moves every brand.
3. **Add a primitive once, in `@t2000/ui`.** If two apps need the same component/token, it belongs in the package, not copy-pasted. (See `engineering-principles.mdc` — single source of truth.)
4. **Bumping `@t2000/ui` is a cross-brand change.** A token/primitive edit ripples to t2000 web, gateway, AND audric. Publish + bump all consumers; smoke each brand.
5. **Brand-specific tokens stay in the app.** Audric's cyan `--signal`, AudricMark, etc. live in `audric/apps/web-v2/app/globals.css` + `audric/.cursor/rules/design-system.mdc` — not in `@t2000/ui`.

